{"name":"Uurthar Caegrax","size":"medium","type":"humanoid","tag":"Dragonborn","alignment":"Lawful Good","hitDice":"24","armorName":"plate","shieldBonus":2,"natArmorBonus":11,"otherArmorDesc":"16 (studded leather, shield)","speed":"30","burrowSpeed":"0","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"0","hover":false,"swimSpeed":"0","customHP":false,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"112 (15d8 + 45)","speedDesc":"30 ft.","strPoints":"22","dexPoints":"15","conPoints":"18","intPoints":"10","wisPoints":"12","chaPoints":"16","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"0","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"0","telepathy":0,"cr":"10","customCr":"5 (1,800 XP)","customProf":3,"isLegendary":false,"legendariesDescription":"The gladiator can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The gladiator regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.","isLair":false,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, the gladiator can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the gladiator can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"The gladiator can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and it can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isRegional":false,"regionalDescription":"The region containing the gladiator's lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the gladiator dies, the first two effects fade over the course of 3d10 days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Brave","desc":"Uurthar has advantage on saving throws against being frightened."},{"name":"Brute","desc":"A melee weapon deals one extra die of its damage when Uurthar hits with it (included in the attack)."},{"name":"Magic Resistance","desc":"Uurthar has advantage on saving throws against spells of the illusion and enchantment schools while you holding his spear."},{"name":"Magic Weapons","desc":"The Uurthar's weapon attacks are magical."}],"actions":[{"name":"Multiattack","desc":"Uurthar makes three melee attacks or two ranged attacks."},{"name":"Dreamer's Thorn","desc":"_Melee or Ranged Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, reach 5 ft. and range 20/60 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [STR 2D6] piercing damage, or [STR 2D8] piercing damage if used with two hands to make a melee attack."},{"name":"Shield Bash","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, reach 5 ft., one creature. _Hit:_ [STR 2D4] bludgeoning damage. If the target is a Medium or smaller creature, it must succeed on a DC 15 Strength saving throw or be knocked prone."},{"name":"Destroy Illusion","desc":"Uurthar dispels an illusion or enchantment spell affecting a creature he touches as a bonus action, spending 2 charges of the Dreamer's Thorn."},{"name":"Breath Weapon (Recharges after a Short or Long Rest)","desc":"Uurthar exhales fire in a 15-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a DC 16 (8 + Con + Pro.) Dexterity saving throw, taking [5D6] fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one."},{"name":"Leadership (Recharges after a Short or Long Rest)","desc":"For 1 minute, Uurthar can utter a special command or warning whenever a nonhostile creature that he can see within 30 ft. of him makes an attack roll or a saving throw. The creature can add a d4 to its roll provided it can hear and understand Uurthar. A creature can benefit from only one Leadership die at a time. This effect ends if Uurthar is incapacitated."},{"name":"Blink","desc":"Uurthar can call upon the power of his ancestors to blink forward at blazing speed. As a bonus action, Uurthar can move up to half his movement in any direction nearly instantly. Opportunity attacks made against Uurthar during this movement are at disadvantage. Any traps based on movement (such as grease or webs) are twice as effective against Uurthar (including